text:
Played last night. 

- balthor is no good. To be more effective i have to go a lot deeper into self mill and thatll make the deck worse. So many time i was missing chainer. Also something else that was relevant is using chainer as gy hate, and i cant use balthor for that. Curiosity satisfied, chainer stays

- grenzo goad/exile was a lot of fun and pretty effective. I had some really explosive starts. Need to tune it a bit: i pretty much never want to sacrifice my dudes, in where i had a bunch of sac outlets earlier. Going to take them all out in favor of having more dudes in the deck. I had cards like the immortal sun in the deck but i always had trouble getting to 6 mana and finding a convenient time. I think i need to lower the curve overall. I got mana screwed several times.... need to think about that more and get help from yall. 
- niv mizzet really sucks against my friends muldrotha deck.
What are the best ways to prevent mana screw in mono red? Maybe to smooth out draws etc. sword of the animist seems really bad on tempo
Moxen
Coldsteel Heart, Diamond, Medallion
Yeah i think i will put more mox in. I had diamond and that mught be the worst one

I think one of the things I like about David Simon's writing for TV is he tends to write about the minutia of really specialized thing, whether it's cops and dealers and junkies in the Wire or musicians and chefs in Treme. I like seeing the nuts and bolts, and there's an element of that to people explaining how their deck worked, what the flaws are, and how they wanna fix it.
could be an interesting idea for a article series
